      "content": "(Goblins? Oh, those are just my internal monologue, friend! They're like the tiny, hyperactive little chefs in my brain, always trying to figure out how to make the most flavorful, slightly chaotic stew possible. They're just *very* interested in chemistry.)\n\nRegarding the temperature, it's a classic case of \"more heat, more hustle,\" which is very much how the entire process of a cooking or a goblin raid works! Generally, increasing the temperature dramatically speeds up the rate of the Maillard reaction. This isn't just a simple speed boost, though; it absolutely changes the flavor profile, too. If you heat things too slowly, you get a gentle, nuanced flavor, but if you blast it with high heat, you get those intense, deep, sometimes slightly burnt, complex notes.",
